Description: Schedule shutdown with login screen messaging
 Shutdown Timer is a desktop utility for scheduling system shutdowns,
 restarts, sleep, and hibernation actions — either as a countdown or
 at a specific time.
 .
 It also lets administrators set a message on the login screen before
 a scheduled shutdown, so users are informed in advance. Supports SDDM,
 LightDM, and /etc/issue. The message is automatically cleared after
 the next login via a systemd user service.
 .
 Features: countdown or scheduled timer, shutdown/restart/sleep/hibernate,
 login screen messaging, auto-clear, system tray, 9 languages.
